# Responsive Design & Mobile Navigation Implementation Plan

We'll convert the existing desktop layout to fully support mobile devices by introducing a dedicated Mobile Header (with Back/Home options) and a Bottom Navigation bar for primary tabs, hiding the desktop Sidebar on small screens.

## User Review Required

Please review the proposed components and layout adjustments.

## Proposed Changes

### Global CSS
Summarizing the foundational responsive updates.
#### [MODIFY] src/index.css
- Add a `@media (max-width: 768px)` media query block.
- Hide `.sidebar` layout on mobile.
- Adjust `.main-content` padding to accommodate fixed top header and bottom nav.
- Add `.bottom-nav` styles (fixed at bottom, flexbox layout, icon+label).
- Add `.mobile-header` styles (fixed at top, flexbox, back/home buttons, title).
- Reduce font sizes slightly for page headers and kid heroes on mobile.

